channel.name: Can the contract state be set to a different value for every deployment?

messages.content: For this case, I have a static injector class and provide inputs via Provable.witness(). I am wondering if this is an acceptable approach 🤔 (looks pretty good)
Thanks a lot! Can you share what the code for deployment looks like? The one that calls Mina.transaction and zkApp.deploy?
Hey @DFST one thing to note is that init() is already called by deploy. So you don't call it a second time.

Unfortunately, this does not work. It generates three account updates (one of those updates does have non-zero key and value data), but the final state is all zeros:

https://berkeley.minaexplorer.com/wallet/B62qraTHXh4HyVUkRkVkZoD4Ga6tWMRB6VQSqL2asgXcAKWBwnvqegZ

The final working code:
https://github.com/dfstio/minanft-lib/blob/master/test/deploy.test.ts

For me it created only 2: one for the account creation fee and the second one to deploy
what o1js library version do you use? Mine is 0.13.1
Can you share the code which generated those 3 account updates?

The code and the result of it's execution:
https://berkeley.minaexplorer.com/wallet/B62qpXjT6o6Ps4XxTcqaFEsZs9xAkXrAE9R3cpkMVJHs9uk8ZrTT8A5
What is the purpose of that init method?
To test how its presence changes the behavior. Can be omitted
Then try to omit it, or at least remove the @method decorator. I think that's why you have an extra account update.

Yes, it works now! Thanks a lot!

https://berkeley.minaexplorer.com/wallet/B62qqkx7b7PCRTiyW71pYQ8qsod3HMzrV5x19rt6pBYJ66v24PgGXSm

I've updated the code to reflect the two working solutions that we have now. Thanks, @Faserisko , for your great support in finding an elegant and working solution!
